{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1600,"text":"I am British."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":5720,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":8880,"text":"Never before has the phrase\n\"I am British\" elicited so much pity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":14800,"text":"I come from an island\nwhere many of us like to believe"},{"time":17560,"text":"there's been a lot of continuity\nover the last thousand years."},{"time":21400,"text":"We tend to have historically\nimposed change on others"},{"time":24160,"text":"but done much less of it ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27360,"text":"So it came as an immense shock to me"},{"time":29840,"text":"when I woke up on the morning of June 24"},{"time":32640,"text":"to discover that my country\nhad voted to leave the European Union,"},{"time":36520,"text":"my Prime Minister had resigned,"},{"time":38400,"text":"and Scotland was considering a referendum"},{"time":41000,"text":"that could bring to an end\nthe very existence of the United Kingdom."},{"time":46920,"text":"So that was an immense shock for me,"},{"time":49880,"text":"and it was an immense\nshock for many people,"},{"time":53080,"text":"but it was also something\nthat, over the following several days,"},{"time":56560,"text":"created a complete political meltdown"},{"time":59320,"text":"in my country."},{"time":60800,"text":"There were calls for a second referendum,"},{"time":63040,"text":"almost as if, following a sports match,"},{"time":65600,"text":"we could ask the opposition for a replay."},{"time":68880,"text":"Everybody was blaming everybody else."},{"time":71360,"text":"People blamed the Prime Minister"},{"time":72960,"text":"for calling the referendum\nin the first place."},{"time":75160,"text":"They blamed the leader of the opposition\nfor not fighting it hard enough."},{"time":78640,"text":"The young accused the old."},{"time":79920,"text":"The educated blamed\nthe less well-educated."},{"time":83440,"text":"That complete meltdown was made even worse"},{"time":86560,"text":"by the most tragic element of it:"},{"time":88680,"text":"levels of xenophobia and racist abuse\nin the streets of Britain"},{"time":92560,"text":"at a level that I have never seen before"},{"time":94840,"text":"in my lifetime."},{"time":97800,"text":"People are now talking about whether\nmy country is becoming a Little England,"},{"time":102200,"text":"or, as one of my colleagues put it,"},{"time":104320,"text":"whether we're about to become\na 1950s nostalgia theme park"},{"time":108520,"text":"floating in the Atlantic Ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113840,"text":"But my question is really,"},{"time":116400,"text":"should we have the degree of shock\nthat we've experienced since?"},{"time":121440,"text":"Was it something\nthat took place overnight?"},{"time":123840,"text":"Or are there deeper structural factors\nthat have led us to where we are today?"},{"time":128360,"text":"So I want to take a step back\nand ask two very basic questions."},{"time":132960,"text":"First, what does Brexit represent,"},{"time":135880,"text":"not just for my country,"},{"time":137440,"text":"but for all of us around the world?"},{"time":140200,"text":"And second, what can we do about it?"},{"time":143400,"text":"How should we all respond?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145760,"text":"So first, what does Brexit represent?"},{"time":148960,"text":"Hindsight is a wonderful thing."},{"time":151840,"text":"Brexit teaches us many things\nabout our society"},{"time":155920,"text":"and about societies around the world."},{"time":159400,"text":"It highlights in ways\nthat we seem embarrassingly unaware of"},{"time":162640,"text":"how divided our societies are."},{"time":164840,"text":"The vote split along lines of age,\neducation, class and geography."},{"time":171200,"text":"Young people didn't turn out\nto vote in great numbers,"},{"time":174120,"text":"but those that did wanted to remain."},{"time":176360,"text":"Older people really wanted\nto leave the European Union."},{"time":180120,"text":"Geographically, it was London and Scotland\nthat most strongly committed"},{"time":183640,"text":"to being part of the European Union,"},{"time":185680,"text":"while in other parts of the country\nthere was very strong ambivalence."},{"time":191000,"text":"Those divisions are things we really\nneed to recognize and take seriously."},{"time":195400,"text":"But more profoundly,\nthe vote teaches us something"},{"time":198280,"text":"about the nature of politics today."},{"time":200640,"text":"Contemporary politics\nis no longer just about right and left."},{"time":204920,"text":"It's no longer just about tax and spend."},{"time":207680,"text":"It's about globalization."},{"time":209640,"text":"The fault line of contemporary politics is\nbetween those that embrace globalization"},{"time":214480,"text":"and those that fear globalization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218320,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":223680,"text":"If we look at why\nthose who wanted to leave --"},{"time":226360,"text":"we call them \"Leavers,\"\nas opposed to \"Remainers\" --"},{"time":228920,"text":"we see two factors in the opinion polls"},{"time":231160,"text":"that really mattered."},{"time":232560,"text":"The first was immigration,\nand the second sovereignty,"},{"time":235920,"text":"and these represent a desire for people\nto take back control of their own lives"},{"time":241400,"text":"and the feeling that they\nare unrepresented by politicians."},{"time":246560,"text":"But those ideas are ones\nthat signify fear and alienation."},{"time":251960,"text":"They represent a retreat\nback towards nationalism and borders"},{"time":257000,"text":"in ways that many of us would reject."},{"time":259600,"text":"What I want to suggest is the picture\nis more complicated than that,"},{"time":262840,"text":"that liberal internationalists,"},{"time":264400,"text":"like myself, and I firmly\ninclude myself in that picture,"},{"time":267640,"text":"need to write ourselves\nback into the picture"},{"time":270200,"text":"in order to understand\nhow we've got to where we are today."},{"time":275200,"text":"When we look at the voting patterns\nacross the United Kingdom,"},{"time":278320,"text":"we can visibly see the divisions."},{"time":281240,"text":"The blue areas show Remain"},{"time":283600,"text":"and the red areas Leave."},{"time":285720,"text":"When I looked at this,"},{"time":287000,"text":"what personally struck me\nwas the very little time in my life"},{"time":290880,"text":"I've actually spent\nin many of the red areas."},{"time":294120,"text":"I suddenly realized that,\nlooking at the top 50 areas in the UK"},{"time":299280,"text":"that have the strongest Leave vote,"},{"time":301160,"text":"I've spent a combined total\nof four days of my life in those areas."},{"time":307560,"text":"In some of those places,"},{"time":309080,"text":"I didn't even know the names\nof the voting districts."},{"time":312680,"text":"It was a real shock to me,"},{"time":314560,"text":"and it suggested that people like me"},{"time":316640,"text":"who think of ourselves\nas inclusive, open and tolerant,"},{"time":320760,"text":"perhaps don't know\nour own countries and societies"},{"time":323480,"text":"nearly as well as we like to believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326120,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":336200,"text":"And the challenge that comes from that\nis we need to find a new way"},{"time":340000,"text":"to narrate globalization to those people,"},{"time":343120,"text":"to recognize that for those people who\nhave not necessarily been to university,"},{"time":347520,"text":"who haven't necessarily\ngrown up with the Internet,"},{"time":349960,"text":"that don't get opportunities to travel,"},{"time":352000,"text":"they may be unpersuaded\nby the narrative that we find persuasive"},{"time":355880,"text":"in our often liberal bubbles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358520,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":363880,"text":"It means that we need to reach out\nmore broadly and understand."},{"time":367520,"text":"In the Leave vote, a minority have peddled\nthe politics of fear and hatred,"},{"time":373560,"text":"creating lies and mistrust"},{"time":376080,"text":"around, for instance,\nthe idea that the vote on Europe"},{"time":379040,"text":"could reduce the number of refugees\nand asylum-seekers coming to Europe,"},{"time":383200,"text":"when the vote on leaving\nhad nothing to do with immigration"},{"time":386480,"text":"from outside the European Union."},{"time":389120,"text":"But for a significant majority\nof the Leave voters"},{"time":392680,"text":"the concern was disillusionment\nwith the political establishment."},{"time":396360,"text":"This was a protest vote for many,"},{"time":398560,"text":"a sense that nobody represented them,"},{"time":401040,"text":"that they couldn't find\na political party that spoke for them,"},{"time":404480,"text":"and so they rejected\nthat political establishment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409440,"text":"This replicates around Europe\nand much of the liberal democratic world."},{"time":414520,"text":"We see it with the rise in popularity\nof Donald Trump in the United States,"},{"time":419440,"text":"with the growing nationalism\nof Viktor Orb√°n in Hungary,"},{"time":423520,"text":"with the increase in popularity\nof Marine Le Pen in France."},{"time":428240,"text":"The specter of Brexit\nis in all of our societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433080,"text":"So the question I think we need to ask\nis my second question,"},{"time":436120,"text":"which is how should we\ncollectively respond?"},{"time":439280,"text":"For all of us who care about creating\nliberal, open, tolerant societies,"},{"time":445280,"text":"we urgently need a new vision,"},{"time":447960,"text":"a vision of a more tolerant,\ninclusive globalization,"},{"time":451680,"text":"one that brings people with us\nrather than leaving them behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456640,"text":"That vision of globalization"},{"time":458600,"text":"is one that has to start by a recognition\nof the positive benefits of globalization."},{"time":463440,"text":"The consensus amongst economists"},{"time":466040,"text":"is that free trade,\nthe movement of capital,"},{"time":468840,"text":"the movement of people across borders"},{"time":470800,"text":"benefit everyone on aggregate."},{"time":473560,"text":"The consensus amongst\ninternational relations scholars"},{"time":476280,"text":"is that globalization\nbrings interdependence,"},{"time":478920,"text":"which brings cooperation and peace."},{"time":481880,"text":"But globalization\nalso has redistributive effects."},{"time":486360,"text":"It creates winners and losers."},{"time":489120,"text":"To take the example of migration,"},{"time":491280,"text":"we know that immigration is a net positive\nfor the economy as a whole"},{"time":494960,"text":"under almost all circumstances."},{"time":498360,"text":"But we also have to be very aware"},{"time":501160,"text":"that there are\nredistributive consequences,"},{"time":504240,"text":"that importantly, low-skilled immigration"},{"time":507720,"text":"can lead to a reduction in wages\nfor the most impoverished in our societies"},{"time":512159,"text":"and also put pressure on house prices."},{"time":514320,"text":"That doesn't detract\nfrom the fact that it's positive,"},{"time":516880,"text":"but it means more people\nhave to share in those benefits"},{"time":519799,"text":"and recognize them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523200,"text":"In 2002, the former Secretary-General\nof the United Nations, Kofi Annan,"},{"time":528120,"text":"gave a speech at Yale University,"},{"time":531040,"text":"and that speech was on the topic\nof inclusive globalization."},{"time":535040,"text":"That was the speech\nin which he coined that term."},{"time":538120,"text":"And he said, and I paraphrase,"},{"time":540920,"text":"\"The glass house of globalization\nhas to be open to all"},{"time":546280,"text":"if it is to remain secure."},{"time":549280,"text":"Bigotry and ignorance"},{"time":552560,"text":"are the ugly face of exclusionary\nand antagonistic globalization.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":559160,"text":"That idea of inclusive globalization\nwas briefly revived in 2008"},{"time":564360,"text":"in a conference on progressive governance"},{"time":566960,"text":"involving many of the leaders\nof European countries."},{"time":571160,"text":"But amid austerity\nand the financial crisis of 2008,"},{"time":575160,"text":"the concept disappeared\nalmost without a trace."},{"time":578280,"text":"Globalization has been taken\nto support a neoliberal agenda."},{"time":582760,"text":"It's perceived to be\npart of an elite agenda"},{"time":585720,"text":"rather than something that benefits all."},{"time":588320,"text":"And it needs to be reclaimed\non a far more inclusive basis"},{"time":591960,"text":"than it is today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593720,"text":"So the question is,\nhow can we achieve that goal?"},{"time":597480,"text":"How can we balance on the one hand\naddressing fear and alienation"},{"time":602240,"text":"while on the other hand\nrefusing vehemently"},{"time":605680,"text":"to give in to xenophobia and nationalism?"},{"time":609480,"text":"That is the question for all of us."},{"time":611640,"text":"And I think, as a social scientist,"},{"time":613480,"text":"that social science\noffers some places to start."},{"time":617000,"text":"Our transformation has to be about\nboth ideas and about material change,"},{"time":622240,"text":"and I want to give you four ideas\nas a starting point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625880,"text":"The first relates to the idea\nof civic education."},{"time":630440,"text":"What stands out from Brexit"},{"time":632240,"text":"is the gap between public perception\nand empirical reality."},{"time":636320,"text":"It's been suggested that we've moved\nto a postfactual society,"},{"time":640040,"text":"where evidence and truth no longer matter,"},{"time":642720,"text":"and lies have equal status\nto the clarity of evidence."},{"time":646840,"text":"So how can we --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":648120,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":650840,"text":"How can we rebuild respect for truth\nand evidence into our liberal democracies?"},{"time":656040,"text":"It has to begin with education,"},{"time":658000,"text":"but it has to start with the recognition\nthat there are huge gaps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662440,"text":"In 2014, the pollster Ipsos MORI"},{"time":666640,"text":"published a survey\non attitudes to immigration,"},{"time":669960,"text":"and it showed that as numbers\nof immigrants increase,"},{"time":674000,"text":"so public concern\nwith immigration also increases,"},{"time":677240,"text":"although it obviously\ndidn't unpack causality,"},{"time":679680,"text":"because this could equally be to do\nnot so much with numbers"},{"time":682840,"text":"but the political\nand media narrative around it."},{"time":685800,"text":"But the same survey also revealed"},{"time":689600,"text":"huge public misinformation"},{"time":691760,"text":"and misunderstanding\nabout the nature of immigration."},{"time":695520,"text":"For example, in these attitudes\nin the United Kingdom,"},{"time":698760,"text":"the public believed that levels of asylum"},{"time":701520,"text":"were a greater proportion\nof immigration than they were,"},{"time":704960,"text":"but they also believed\nthe levels of educational migration"},{"time":708440,"text":"were far lower as a proportion\nof overall migration"},{"time":711560,"text":"than they actually are."},{"time":713080,"text":"So we have to address this misinformation,"},{"time":715760,"text":"the gap between perception and reality\non key aspects of globalization."},{"time":720280,"text":"And that can't just be something\nthat's left to our schools,"},{"time":723120,"text":"although that's important\nto begin at an early age."},{"time":725560,"text":"It has to be about lifelong\ncivic participation"},{"time":728640,"text":"and public engagement\nthat we all encourage as societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"The second thing\nthat I think is an opportunity"},{"time":736800,"text":"is the idea to encourage more interaction\nacross diverse communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741440,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":745760,"text":"One of the things that stands out\nfor me very strikingly,"},{"time":748760,"text":"looking at immigration attitudes\nin the United Kingdom,"},{"time":751640,"text":"is that ironically,\nthe regions of my country"},{"time":754440,"text":"that are the most tolerant of immigrants"},{"time":756369,"text":"have the highest numbers of immigrants."},{"time":759160,"text":"So for instance, London and the Southeast\nhave the highest numbers of immigrants,"},{"time":763520,"text":"and they are also by far\nthe most tolerant areas."},{"time":766680,"text":"It's those areas of the country\nthat have the lowest levels of immigration"},{"time":770320,"text":"that actually are the most exclusionary\nand intolerant towards migrants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775400,"text":"So we need to encourage exchange programs."},{"time":777760,"text":"We need to ensure that older generations\nwho maybe can't travel"},{"time":781240,"text":"get access to the Internet."},{"time":783400,"text":"We need to encourage,\neven on a local and national level,"},{"time":786120,"text":"more movement, more participation,"},{"time":788000,"text":"more interaction\nwith people who we don't know"},{"time":790720,"text":"and whose views we might\nnot necessarily agree with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794880,"text":"The third thing that I think\nis crucial, though,"},{"time":797240,"text":"and this is really fundamental,"},{"time":799040,"text":"is we have to ensure that everybody shares"},{"time":801360,"text":"in the benefits of globalization."},{"time":804520,"text":"This illustration from the Financial Times\npost-Brexit is really striking."},{"time":809280,"text":"It shows tragically that those people\nwho voted to leave the European Union"},{"time":813040,"text":"were those who actually\nbenefited the most materially"},{"time":815880,"text":"from trade with the European Union."},{"time":819080,"text":"But the problem is\nthat those people in those areas"},{"time":821640,"text":"didn't perceive themselves\nto be beneficiaries."},{"time":824320,"text":"They didn't believe that they\nwere actually getting access"},{"time":827120,"text":"to material benefits of increased trade\nand increased mobility around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833800,"text":"I work on questions\npredominantly to do with refugees,"},{"time":837600,"text":"and one of the ideas\nI spent a lot of my time preaching,"},{"time":840280,"text":"mainly to developing countries\naround the world,"},{"time":843080,"text":"is that in order to encourage\nthe integration of refugees,"},{"time":846680,"text":"we can't just benefit\nthe refugee populations,"},{"time":849040,"text":"we also have to address the concerns\nof the host communities in local areas."},{"time":855480,"text":"But in looking at that,"},{"time":856840,"text":"one of the policy prescriptions\nis that we have to provide"},{"time":859880,"text":"disproportionately better\neducation facilities, health facilities,"},{"time":863520,"text":"access to social services"},{"time":865320,"text":"in those regions of high immigration"},{"time":867600,"text":"to address the concerns\nof those local populations."},{"time":870440,"text":"But while we encourage that\naround the developing world,"},{"time":873120,"text":"we don't take those lessons home"},{"time":874720,"text":"and incorporate them in our own societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878520,"text":"Furthermore, if we're going\nto really take seriously"},{"time":881560,"text":"the need to ensure people share\nin the economic benefits,"},{"time":884920,"text":"our businesses and corporations\nneed a model of globalization"},{"time":888600,"text":"that recognizes that they, too,\nhave to take people with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893440,"text":"The fourth and final idea\nI want to put forward"},{"time":896520,"text":"is an idea that we need\nmore responsible politics."},{"time":900080,"text":"There's very little\nsocial science evidence"},{"time":903240,"text":"that compares attitudes on globalization."},{"time":906080,"text":"But from the surveys that do exist,"},{"time":908640,"text":"what we can see is there's huge variation\nacross different countries"},{"time":913400,"text":"and time periods in those countries"},{"time":915720,"text":"for attitudes and tolerance"},{"time":917120,"text":"of questions like migration\nand mobility on the one hand"},{"time":920840,"text":"and free trade on the other."},{"time":922920,"text":"But one hypothesis that I think emerges\nfrom a cursory look at that data"},{"time":928200,"text":"is the idea that polarized societies\nare far less tolerant of globalization."},{"time":934320,"text":"It's the societies\nlike Sweden in the past,"},{"time":937160,"text":"like Canada today,"},{"time":938600,"text":"where there is a centrist politics,"},{"time":940440,"text":"where right and left work together,"},{"time":942520,"text":"that we encourage supportive attitudes\ntowards globalization."},{"time":946560,"text":"And what we see around the world today\nis a tragic polarization,"},{"time":950400,"text":"a failure to have dialogue\nbetween the extremes in politics,"},{"time":953440,"text":"and a gap in terms\nof that liberal center ground"},{"time":956240,"text":"that can encourage communication\nand a shared understanding."},{"time":960080,"text":"We might not achieve that today,"},{"time":961720,"text":"but at the very least we have to call\nupon our politicians and our media"},{"time":965560,"text":"to drop a language of fear\nand be far more tolerant of one another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":969360,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":977800,"text":"These ideas are very tentative,"},{"time":980600,"text":"and that's in part because this needs\nto be an inclusive and shared project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"I am still British."},{"time":988920,"text":"I am still European."},{"time":991640,"text":"I am still a global citizen."},{"time":995200,"text":"For those of us who believe"},{"time":997240,"text":"that our identities\nare not mutually exclusive,"},{"time":1001360,"text":"we have to all work together"},{"time":1004400,"text":"to ensure that globalization\ntakes everyone with us"},{"time":1008120,"text":"and doesn't leave people behind."},{"time":1010360,"text":"Only then will we truly reconcile\ndemocracy and globalization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1015960,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017200,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}